## When to use

Use this skill when the developer wants to:
- Build a complete Xsolla-powered game shop from scratch
- Set up a headless webshop with catalog, payments, and auth
- Walk through the full Xsolla integration checklist
- Launch a working shop in sandbox end-to-end

Do NOT use this skill for single-domain tasks (e.g. "just add a payment method") — use the relevant domain skill directly instead.

## Prerequisites

```bash
export XSOLLA_API_KEY=<your-sandbox-key>
export MERCHANT_ID=<your-merchant-id>
export XSOLLA_ENV=sandbox
```

You will need an Xsolla Publisher Account. Create one at https://publisher.xsolla.com/signup if you don't have one.

## Steps

This skill chains the following domain skills in order. Run each to completion before moving to the next.

1. **`project-init`** — Create an Xsolla project and configure merchant settings
2. **`login-setup`** — Integrate Xsolla Login or NewID authentication
3. **`catalog-design`** — Configure virtual catalog: items, pricing, virtual currency, bundles
4. **`shop-design`** — Apply branding, theme tokens, and LLM-assisted visual design
5. **`payments-config`** — Integrate Pay Station and configure payment methods
6. **`webhooks-impl`** — Implement webhook handlers for order and payment events
7. **`store-build`** — Deploy WebShop, Site Builder storefront, or headless FE

After completing all steps, run an end-to-end sandbox transaction to verify the full flow.

## Common pitfalls

- **Wrong order**: `login-setup` must come before `payments-config` — Pay Station needs an auth token
- **Missing PROJECT_ID**: After `project-init`, set `PROJECT_ID` in your environment before running subsequent skills
- **Sandbox vs production**: Keep `XSOLLA_ENV=sandbox` until the full flow is verified — production webhooks cannot be easily rolled back
